1
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:18,184
I've met plenty of people who turned out
to be nice once I talked to them.

2
00:00:18,768 --> 00:00:21,688
People often said I was hard to approach.

3
00:00:24,774 --> 00:00:27,986
I'm terrible at starting conversations.

4
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:30,196
I'm glad we can talk about manga together.

5
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:37,704
It's been boring
because there's no one I click with.

6
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:42,584
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

7
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,795
-Thank you. Thank you.
-Thank you. Thank you.

8
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:47,756
Don't mention it.

9
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:53,553
If the environment is partly to blame
for the isolation,

10
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:56,014
I would…

11
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:58,558
HAMBURGER BOM BOM

12
00:00:58,641 --> 00:00:59,809
Yeah. Then, this guy…

13
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,228
Amamiya? You listening?

14
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:04,689
'Course I am.

15
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,941
Oh, well.

16
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:42,954
EPISODE 2
LOCKSMITH

17
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:45,081
Join us for a good time.

18
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,207
No, thanks!

19
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,834
What do I even do?

20
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:49,252
TWO AGAINST ONE
WHAT IF I UPSET THEM

21
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:50,336
I'm terrified and angry.

22
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,713
THEY'RE MOCKING ME
WHAT A WASTE OF TIME

23
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:53,715
-How frustrating.
-Let's go.

24
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:55,008
-Come with us.
-It's gonna be fun.

25
00:02:55,091 --> 00:02:57,802
I said I'm not interested!

26
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:01,806
I'm serious. Leave me alone.

27
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:05,852
Bye.

28
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:09,898
Sorry. You okay?

29
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,234
I thought it was you.

30
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:16,070
Mr. Giraffe?

31
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:18,239
I HAVE TO TAKE THE CROSSWALK
OVER THERE TO GET TO THIS SIDE

32
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:19,657
Sorry I ignored you back there.

33
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:24,245
Please pretend like we're friends.

34
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:25,830
I'm sorry,

35
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:28,833
but please stay with me
until we're out of their sight.

36
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:30,335
Say what?

37
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:34,672
I was able to meet up with a friend,
so I'm okay now. Bye!

38
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:35,757
What?

39
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:39,385
BLURRY

40
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:42,138
Does she know them?

41
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,390
Maybe not.

42
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:47,185
SCURRYING AWAY

43
00:03:47,268 --> 00:03:49,062
High schoolers these days are scary.

44
00:03:49,145 --> 00:03:50,146
Ain't that right.

45
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:54,400
Thank you so much.

46
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,904
Huh? I didn't do anything, did I?

47
00:03:57,987 --> 00:04:00,156
Didn't you know them?

48
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,743
They came up to me out of nowhere.

49
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,246
You're so popular.

50
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,414
-It's not like that.
-What?

51
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,376
I mean,

52
00:04:11,876 --> 00:04:14,754
what you saw wasn't like that.

53
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:20,176
Their vibe was that nothing else mattered
as long as they were having a good time.

54
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:23,513
Rather, they were looking down on me,

55
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:26,933
so it's not a situation
I can be happy about. So…

56
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:33,022
Hold on, why am I defending myself?

57
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:35,316
I should just play it off.

58
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,694
He's gonna get weirded out.

59
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:42,991
Should I have punched them?

60
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,244
No, you don't need to take it that far.

61
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:47,704
Are you sure?

62
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:52,417
Actually, I'm sorry. It's like
I used you to get away from them.

63
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:55,712
Why are you apologizing?
It's totally fine.

64
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:58,840
I wouldn't get upset
over something like this.

65
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,261
Do you live around here, Himuro?

66
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:05,888
No. I wanted to go
to the community center.

67
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:08,099
What? That's where I was going too.

68
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:10,101
Then, why don't we walk together?

69
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:23,906
Extracurricular activities will be on hold
during the exam preparation period…

70
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,701
-HR is going on forever!
-…so your daily routine may be disrupted.

71
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:29,871
Koyun, sorry I'm making you wait!

72
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:32,874
Say…

73
00:05:37,086 --> 00:05:39,547
I'd like to know your name, please.

74
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:42,842
Right. I never told you my name.

75
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:43,968
My bad.

76
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:47,513
You can just call me Yota.

77
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,682
He only gave me his first name.

78
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:50,767
I WANTED TO KNOW HIS LAST NAME

79
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,769
It's a pleasure to meet you, Himuro.

80
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:55,271
Sorry.

81
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:58,858
My last name's actually Hikawa,
not Himuro.

82
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,818
No way! Sorry.

83
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:02,779
You should've told me sooner.

84
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:10,286
How much longer is it to get
to the community center?

85
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:12,205
I'm terrible with maps.

86
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:14,373
We'll be there in about five minutes.

87
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,292
Five minutes.

88
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,462
Can we keep
the conversation going for that long?

89
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:27,804
Hikawa, are you good friends with Miki?

90
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:31,599
We're childhood friends.

91
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:34,185
We live close, and we went to the same
elementary and middle school.

92
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:36,062
Is that so?

93
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,483
We went to the same cram school
in middle school.

94
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,567
What?

95
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:44,195
They've been friends since middle school?

96
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:47,448
Does that mean he knows the real Miki?

97
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,117
Now Miki.

98
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,243
You know, Miki,

99
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:53,704
I liked her much better
the way she used to be.

100
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,540
Me too.

101
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:56,624
Right?

102
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:59,168
Honestly, I want to tell everyone
what she's really like.

103
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,379
Seriously, what a waste.

104
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:04,590
No matter what you're like,

105
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,093
some people will want to stick by you.

106
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,181
You've gotta be kidding.

107
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:15,268
Hold on, isn't that Yota?

108
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:17,937
You're right.

109
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:20,356
But wait. That girl next to him, she's…

110
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,609
What?

111
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:25,611
MEITEN COMMUNITY CENTER

112
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,742
Here's your seat, Miki.

113
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:32,910
Thanks.

114
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:36,247
What the… What kind of pairing is this?

115
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,291
What kind…

116
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:39,584
Great question.

117
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:43,504
What?

118
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:46,132
Hey, I'm the one asking.

119
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:51,762
Sorry.

120
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:56,559
Geez! You guys surprised me!

121
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:59,020
Why didn't you give me a heads up?

122
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,355
I told her not to say anything.

123
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:02,857
I told her, "Let's surprise Miki!"

124
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:05,693
You too, Koyun.
Why'd you go along with it?

125
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:10,573
More importantly,
didn't you punch the jerks who hit on her?

126
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:13,284
No. Hikawa didn't want me to.

127
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:16,037
There's no need to go that far.

128
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,163
What?

129
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:21,375
Are you taking the same train?
I'll walk you to the station.

130
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:22,835
Thanks!

131
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,589
Yota, do you go to that study room often?

132
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:28,257
Yeah.

133
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:31,302
My younger brother and sister
are still little.

134
00:08:31,385 --> 00:08:33,346
It's too noisy at home.

135
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:35,973
Right. How old are they again?

136
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:38,518
They're both three years old.
They're twins.

137
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,144
HIS MOM IS SUCH A TROOPER…

138
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,729
That's quite an age gap.

139
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:44,941
It's partly because
of the toddlers at home,

140
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:47,235
but I can focus better at the study room.

141
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:50,613
I feel you. I didn't check my phone today!

142
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:52,907
I didn't even have space to fool around.

143
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,492
Don't fool around.

144
00:08:56,577 --> 00:08:58,496
Give me a minute.

145
00:08:58,579 --> 00:09:02,250
I need some sugar to recharge
after all the studying I did.

146
00:09:03,251 --> 00:09:05,253
Great idea. I'll grab a drink too.

147
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,303
He's taller than the vending machine.

148
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:15,513
It must be nice.

149
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:19,267
I wish I was born that way.

150
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,394
Take your pick, you two.

151
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:22,645
You don't mind?

152
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:24,397
I know you want the red bean soup, Miki.

153
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,148
You know me well.

154
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,025
Thanks, Yota.

155
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,152
I'll cover you next time.

156
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,655
Oh, my gosh! Why?

157
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:37,577
You used a bill, so how'd you
manage to scatter coins everywhere?

158
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,412
My bad.

159
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:42,331
What do you want to drink, Hikawa?

160
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:43,666
Me?

161
00:09:43,749 --> 00:09:45,001
I FEEL BAD - SHAKE SHAKE

162
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:46,294
I…

163
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:50,214
Here, Miki. You can pick for her.

164
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:51,507
Leave it to me.

165
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:55,094
How about a warm corn soup for Koyun?

166
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:58,556
But I'm craving red bean soup,
so red bean soup it is!

167
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:00,182
What the heck?

168
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:04,520
Well, I want her to drink the same thing
so we can both say it's tasty.

169
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:06,814
You're so selfish.

170
00:10:08,107 --> 00:10:09,567
They really do get along.

171
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:11,569
RED BEAN SOUP

172
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:17,992
Like I said earlier,
we went to the same cram school.

173
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:21,078
Miki, Minato, and I were always together.

174
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:24,248
Oh, yeah. We used to
eat and talk after cram school.

175
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:27,752
Mina… You mean Amamiya.

176
00:10:27,835 --> 00:10:30,087
Hold on, Koyun, you know Minato too?

177
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:33,090
No, not really.

178
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,967
STRETCH

179
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:38,137
Don't tell me he picked on you again.

180
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:39,221
Again?

181
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,100
You poor thing.

182
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,311
You can just ignore him.

183
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:48,606
Yota, do you not get along with Amamiya?

184
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:51,484
I'm just kidding.

185
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,696
Koyun, Yota and Minato.

186
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:59,867
Hikawa, do people around you
call you Koyun?

187
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:00,951
PEOPLE RARELY CALL HER BY NAME

188
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:02,244
No, only Miki does.

189
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:04,038
-Koyun.
-Yes?

190
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:05,998
It's a good nickname.

191
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:07,375
Right?

192
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:09,001
Why are you smug about it?

193
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:12,880
I told you, you can be casual with me.

194
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:15,049
I don't like people being overly formal.

195
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:16,926
-No more talking so politely.
-What?

196
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,135
I get it.

197
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:21,013
I also feel more comfortable
when people are casual.

198
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:22,973
Is that how it is?

199
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:25,476
Thank you!

200
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:28,270
Yota, will you be
at the study room tomorrow too?

201
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,106
Yeah. I'll be there.

202
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:31,524
Then, see you tomorrow.

203
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:33,359
See you tomorrow.

204
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:36,654
'Til tomorrow.

205
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:55,339
Koyuki Hikawa.

206
00:11:58,384 --> 00:12:00,845
Huh, was there a girl like that?

207
00:12:00,928 --> 00:12:03,681
I think she's Hikawa from Class 2.

208
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,767
Word is, she's always grouchy
and doesn't fit in with her class.

209
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:16,277
I thought Class 2 was pretty quiet.

210
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:21,240
Maybe it's more that she can't find
anyone she can relate to.

211
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:26,745
Since then, I kept following her
with my eyes every time we crossed paths.

212
00:12:27,746 --> 00:12:28,831
She's by herself again.

213
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:33,085
STRETCH

214
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:35,379
I always thought,

215
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:39,383
"What a p…"

216
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,178
INCOMING CALL
NINE AUDIO

217
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,015
Sorry, Minato.

218
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:47,641
Can we meet right now?

219
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:49,101
There's something I want to talk about.

220
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:51,979
Okay. I'll come out.

221
00:13:08,787 --> 00:13:10,247
What's this out of the blue?

222
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:15,461
You must be cold.

223
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:21,967
ROYAL MILK TEA

224
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:23,219
I want to break up.

225
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:29,225
What makes you say that?

226
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:33,729
I can't trust you.

227
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:38,234
You could chalk it up to kindness,

228
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:44,240
but you never liked me to begin with,
did you, Minato?

229
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:48,619
I can tell you're not into me.

230
00:13:48,702 --> 00:13:52,456
Did I do something
that made you feel lonely?

231
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,877
Don't respond
to everything with questions.

232
00:13:56,961 --> 00:14:01,006
You always do that.
I want to know how you really feel.

233
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,347
You know what, Minato?

234
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:12,059
You really don't have a sense of self.

235
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,272
I'm home.

236
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:21,569
Were you out, Minato?
Was it something urgent?

237
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,279
No.

238
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,531
It was nothing, really.

239
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,997
It's gonna be fine, Amamiya.
It must be rough.

240
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,499
Hey, I just got dumped.

241
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,042
Why don't you comfort me a little?

242
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,419
Well, how many times is it now?

243
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:40,129
It's starting to be funny.

244
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:43,215
Though, I'm sure you'll have
a new girlfriend in no time. Darn it, you!

245
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:46,135
Amamiya, you broke up? Again?

246
00:14:46,218 --> 00:14:47,219
Yup.

247
00:14:47,803 --> 00:14:52,600
She called me out when I was studying
last night. Then she broke up with me.

248
00:14:52,683 --> 00:14:53,851
That's rough.

249
00:14:53,934 --> 00:14:57,229
For some reason, I always get dumped.

250
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,232
Why do you think that is?

251
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,694
WE LET OUR GUARD DOWN,
AND THIS AGAIN - THUMP THUMP

252
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,029
Fujita! Don't let him trick you.

253
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:06,947
Don't hold eye contact
for longer than three seconds!

254
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:08,365
Okay.

255
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,243
-I'll hold him down. Now, go!
-Morning… Huh?

256
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,914
Minato, what'd you do this time? Sheesh.

257
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:18,000
I haven't done a thing. Why do you
always assume I've done something wrong?

258
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:21,253
Speaking of…

259
00:15:27,843 --> 00:15:30,971
The cafeteria has a lot more options
if you get there early.

260
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:33,140
-Hey, Yota.
-Yeah?

261
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,644
Weren't you walking home
with Hikawa yesterday?

262
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:38,646
I'm sure he'd say…

263
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:41,982
It's not like that!
It's a misunderstanding!

264
